text: Acleris dealbata is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in Japan (Hokkaido, Honshyu)Croesia at funet and Russia. The wingspan is 13–16 mm.Japanese Moths The larvae feed on Salix species.Tortricidae Food Plant Database ==References== Category:Moths described in 1975 dealbata Category:Moths of Japan Category:Moths of Russia
